Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.13,0:00:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,MARINE-MEDIC. Joint Class VIII and casualty-flow decision support.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.13,0:00:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Casualty in 30 minutes. Supply chain in 30 hours. We close the loop on\Nboth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.14,0:00:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,TCCC and JTS triage, hub-spoke supply check, GCSS-MC requisition, all\Nin one chain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.14,0:00:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One regional med depot at Apra. Twelve distributed Marine units across\NWestPac.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.14,0:00:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Inject the scenario: HE blast MASCAL on a 13th MEU FRSS, twenty-two\NWIA inbound.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.21,0:00:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Six-stage agent chain runs: triage cards stream per WIA in JSON-mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.22,0:00:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Class VIII demand projects time-phased over 1, 6, 12, 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.23,0:00:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hub-spoke check finds the gap. Auto-requisition pops in GCSS-MC\Nformat.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.23,0:00:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A Kamiwaza-deployed hero model writes the Medical Sustainment Action\NBrief.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.23,0:00:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Casualty data stays in IL5 enclave. Hash-chained audit, HIPAA and NDAA\Nflavored.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.24,0:01:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Powered by the Kamiwaza Stack. Deploy in hours, not months.
